- https://github.com/jeffknupp/sandman/issues/34

This commit seemed to make this issue more clear but I guess this was lost when switching to the click library for command-line parsing.
  - https://github.com/jeffknupp/sandman/commit/34406d3797dd567647b78e0cf6a030a4299d68fa

sandmanctl: update help for --host and --port

current text suggests you can set the host/port of the database
that sandman is connecting to here, but in fact, it's the
host/port of sandman itself.

Merge pull request #24 from Tinche/sandmanctl

Misc. sandmanctl changes

Added docopt to installation reqs in setup.py.
Switched sandmanctl to setuptool's entry_points mechanism.
Removed unused imports in sandmanctl.
Switched the URI argument to required (from optional) in sandmanctl.

Use 127.0.0.1 instead of localhost

Localhost might resolve to the ipv6 ::1, but flask only binds to 127.0.0.1 by default. This makes the webbrowser connect to the correct IP.
Fix issue with foreign key references when class name doesn't match table name (closes #12)
fix setup.py to not include circular reference (fixes #11)
add additional content-type test; isolate database interaction to increase modularity
Properly differentiate logic between 'Content-type' and 'Accept' headers and return the appropriate HTTP code in the correct content type when errors occur
test and better support different content-types in request
Stop needlessly passing around response object
update docs with new version number
bump version for Bootstrap theme; updated docs; refactored tests
refactor tests to be more modular
